# DEPRECATED

DESCRIPTION
-----------
*Please note that Hedgehog is no longer actively developed.* 
The DNS-STATS project is now focussing on
a newer data collection (dns-stats-compactor) and presentation solution - see the
http://www.dns-stats.org website.

Hedgehog is a visualisation tool for DNS statistics that consumes data
acquired with the DSC collector.

Hedgehog was initially developed for ICANN by Sinodun IT and is now released
open source. This Source Code Form is subject to the terms of the Mozilla Public
License, v. 2.0. If a copy of the MPL was not distributed with this
file, you can obtain one at https://mozilla.org/MPL/2.0/.


REGISTRATION
-------------
If you use Hedgehog, please consider subscribing to the Users Mailing list:
https://mm.dns-stats.org/mailman/listinfo/dns-stats-users
and providing feedback. It helps us to know how Hedgehog is being used!

OVERVIEW
--------
For general information and the User guide see the Hedgehog website:
https://github.com/dns-stats/hedgehog/wiki

USER GUIDE
----------
Read the User_Guide.pdf in the docs directory for the lastest version or look
online: https://github.com/dns-stats/hedgehog/wiki/Documentation

PACKAGES
---------
The latest Hedgehog packages are available from ppa:dns-stats/presenter

SOURCE INSTALLATION
------------
This is no longer officially supported.

VAGRANT INSTALLATION
------------
You can load Hedgehog locally using a virtual machine and Vagrant 
(https://www.vagrantup.com/downloads) â€” Requires also VirtualBox.
Execute `vagrant up` to build the vm and run provisionning scripts 
(dependencies installation, compilation, configuration).
Once completed, you can access to the server using this url: 
`http://localhost:8080/hedgehog`

SUPPORT
-------
- Mailing list: https://mm.dns-stats.org/mailman/listinfo/dns-stats-users
